  <summary>4/5/2000--Introduced.
Fairness in Amortization of Software Tax Act of 2000 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) make depreciable computer software eligible for section 179 annual expensing; and (2) exempt all computer software from designation as "section 197 intangible" (15-year depreciation).</summary>
